                <note rend="inline" type="source">819.51/190: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Price</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-06T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 8.51 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Panaman Secretary of Treasury yesterday signed contract effective as of February
                    1st with Fiscal Agent Ruan with assurance of approval of Panaman President
                    providing for a two years term and an American assistant at a salary of $6000.
                    Panaman authorities attempted to reserve right of dismissal at any time by
                    payment of two additional months salary but this was changed so as to require
                    payment of salary for balance of term. I gave dinner at Legation last night to
                    Fiscal Agent, Panaman President and Cabinet, officials of Canal Zone, of
                    association of commerce, of Panama railway, and managers of all banks being
                    present.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
